@Katie Mc
Today’s update fixed the crashing on my iPad app. Very grateful, thanks tech folks! 

Great celebratory puzzle. Knew I was looking for the 13 colonies in two letter rebuses early on so it was a lot of fun sussing them out.

@Barry Ancona

Meh. The revealer gives it away. I knew something was up on my first pass, but couldn't figure it out until I saw the revealer. I then knew it had to be the postal codes for the first 13 States.

Obviously I'm not a novice, but I'd counter that this is an excellent intro to rebuses (rebi?) for a novice

@Barry Ancona

James Bond always checks his hotel room for electronic bugs
when he first enters.  Usually he exterminates them; sometimes he feeds them bad information.

@Barry Ancona

I loved this puzzle but I don’t thing the rest of the grid was too easy. The tangle of reasonably obscure musical entries in the SE as well as interesting and uncommon words like PICA, SABOTS, etc made for a nice challenge IMHO. 

To be clear I am *not* complaining (well maybe a little sideeye to that SE corner). I loved this puzzle and solved without lookups. Just saying I think the “this was only east for the newbies” might be overdoing it a bit on this one.

