@R.J. Smith -- Actually, someone other than you DOES care about your streak.  That someone is the NYT.  That's because they hear the cash in the cash register jingling.  If you have a streak to maintain, you're hooked.  You can't stop subscribing.  Ever.

But if you solve the puzzle in the physical paper as I do, you won't know if you do or don't have a streak.  No one will tell you.  You won't think to ask.  And you won't care.  Trust me, you won't.  Once you no longer have it waved in your face every day...

While I'm addicted to the seductive and challenging Phrazle, which is not owned by the NYT, btw, I am rather indifferent to Wordle -- which I find pretty meh.  I forget to do it about as often as I remember, and of course I do it online.  So that every time I go to the site there's a line: "Add to Your One-Day Streak!" or "Add to Your Two-Day Streak!"  Of course that's because I didn't remember to do it.  I want to say: "I don't care about my streak because I don't especially care about this puzzle -- which is why I only have a One-Day or Two Day streak."  OTOH, my streak on my  beloved Phrazle is 1,225 -- not that I care about that aspect.  What I really AM proud of is that I have gotten 717 answers in only two guesses.

@Charles Peterson

I don't think complaints are shouted down either.  There are dozens of complaints in this single forum that have gotten no pushback whatsoever, and many receive support.

I think some people have exceeding thin skin.  Any reply, however worded, is considered being mean or shouting down.

