@Laurie

So I respect that it was hard for you and I respect that you didn’t like it. But the reason it was published was because lots of other people do like it and appreciate the challenge of having to figure out where the rebuses go. It’s a time honored rebus tradition of the past that has only lately started to go by the wayside. 
I’ll leave it at that.

@Jim
I am generally anti outlining the rebuses unless the placements or squished letters are exceptionally obscure. For me, this puzzle's rebuses were mostly pretty obviously identifiable by the crosses. 
E.g., 36A: Washington was President Elect in 1789. ELECT won't fit in 4 squares. Something's gotta give. If you haven't already figured out the 13 colonies trick,  you need the down clues to locate the squish. But if you've grasped the trick, then squishing CT is a gimme.

