@Matt

The short answer is I really don’t care whether I get a gold star or not so I don’t have criteria for what’s “cheating” or not. The long answer is, I will do just about whatever I can to not check puzzle which usually would include running the alphabet, flyspecking, then checking spelling of words or entries I’m not sure of. I consider that a solve for me. Rarely I would do a straight look-up but haven’t had to do that for a long time; if I did I’d consider that a loss, although I’d feel better if it’s a Natick I actually didn’t know vs a stupid mistake. If I couldn’t figure out my mistake I’d look at comments and someone would probably have the same one. But either way I’d have a gold star but I truly haven’t even checked my streak or care.

I will confess that when doing archives and I think I finished but don’t feel like flyspecking I will go ahead and check puzzle. But that’s not so much because the streak doesn’t matter, as I want to have the full experience when I’m commenting on new puzzles so want to feel like I’m putting in the work that everyone else is.

