@Paul
The same way any rebus puzzle is figured out; by noticing that a particular answer that you're fairly sure of doesn't quite fit, then finding a way to get to fit, usually by putting more than one letter in a box. 

In today's puzzle, I knew the answer to 23A had to be BENJAMIN, but it didn't fit. Then it occurred to me that if I put NJ into one box (I do it on paper), that would work. That was my first theme answer, and it told me that they would probably all be state abbreviations.

@Jeff
