I wouldn't particularly disagree if someone opined that perhaps some occasional easier clues might've ideally been tossed in to give a couple "gimmes" more often through this puzzle, replacing more abstruse clues (just one or two maybe), but I still enjoyed it and felt it to be an excellent puzzle. I guess once one catches on to the coliny/ state abbreviation theme it really does help. But no I don't think it was 'unsolvable' without lookups.

